git
===

Init a git repo:
	git init

Or clone one (if ssh key is set up):
	git clone git@github.com:MiTop/testRepo.git

Otherwise use https connections.

Configure User Settings (local settings):
	git config user.email "mladentopic@hotmail.com"
	git config user.name "MiTop"

For example color:
	git config color.ui auto

===

Watch stauts:
	git status

Copy or create a file and:
	git add fileName

Commit changes:
	git commmit -m "Your comment"

Push changes to remote:
	git push

===

What branch are you on and how many are available:
	git branch

Create new branch:
	git checkout -b yourBranchName

Copy from origin to your new branch:
	git push origin yourBranchName

Change branch:
	git checkout yourBranchName

Do changes (add, commit, push)... back to master:
	git checkout master

Merge changes from branch:
	git merge yourBranchName

